  "section": "Math",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Group the terms",
      "content": "Group the polynomial into two pairs.<br/>$$x^8+x^7y+xy^5+y^6=(x^8+x^7y)+(xy^5+y^6)$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Factor each group",
      "content": "Each group has a common factor.<br/>$$x^8+x^7y=x^7(x+y)$$<br/>$$xy^5+y^6=y^5(x+y)$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Factor the common binomial",
      "content": "The two grouped terms now share the factor $x+y$.<br/>$$x^7(x+y)+y^5(x+y)=(x+y)(x^7+y^5)$$<br/>One factor is $x^7+y^5$. The answer is <strong>A</strong>."
    }
  ]
}
